SIMPLE: ignominious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ignominious
<hw>Ig`no*min"i*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ignominiosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ignominieux</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Marked with ignominy; incurring public disgrace;
dishonorable; shameful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then first with fear surprised and sense of pain,⟦br⟧
Fled <qex>ignominious</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deserving ignominy; despicable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One single, obscure, <qex>ignominious</qex> projector.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Humiliating; degrading; <as>as, an
<ex>ignominious</ex> judgment or sentence</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ignominiously</ent>⟦br⟧
